                </h2>

                                    <div class="ctpl-c-faq_accordion-wrapper">
                                <div class="ctpl-c-faq_accordion ">
                                    <button tabindex="0" area-expanded="false" aria-controls="858a3149-2496-455a-8a8a-bca39a364049" id="accordion-id-858a3149-2496-455a-8a8a-bca39a364049" class="ctpl-c-faq_accordion-header">
                                        <div class="ctpl-c-faq_accordion-header-content">
                                            As a worker, how can I request a refund for overpayment of contributions?
                                        </div>
                                        <div aria-hidden="true" class="ctpl-c-faq_accordion-header-button">
                                            <i></i>
                                        </div>
                                    </button>
                                        <div class="ctpl-c-faq_accordion-content" id="858a3149-2496-455a-8a8a-bca39a364049" role="region" aria-labelledby="accordion-id-858a3149-2496-455a-8a8a-bca39a364049" tabindex="0">
                                            If you identify that you have made combined payroll contributions that equal more than the calendar year&rsquo;s maximum payroll deductions for the previous year, then you should submit a request for an employee overpayment reimbursement refund by clicking on the <a href="/contactus">Contact Us</a>&nbsp;tab, selecting &ldquo;Employee Overpayment Reimbursement&rdquo; as the contact reason and completing the customer support ticket.<p>

<p>Upon submission of the request, you will receive a CT Paid Leave Employee Refund Request form with additional detailed instructions. You will be asked to submit the completed CT aid Leave Employee Refund Request Form with the following additional documents so that we can process the refund:&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
    <li>A copy of the final calendar year-end paycheck from every employer</li>
    <li>A copy of the Federal W-2 received from every employer</li>
    <li>A copy of current driver&rsquo;s license or Connecticut State ID for identity verification purposes</li>
</ul>
<p>To see the current Social Security FICA Wage Cap, please visit this website:&nbsp;<a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.ssa.gov/benefits/retirement/planner/maxtax.html" target="_blank" aria-label="Opens the retirement benefits planner on the federal social security website in a new window">Benefits Planner | Social Security Tax Limits on Your Earnings | SSA</a></p>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
                                        </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="ctpl-c-faq_accordion ">
                                    <button tabindex="0" area-expanded="false" aria-controls="df76f8fc-18d1-457a-9486-4e2a7169b12d" id="accordion-id-df76f8fc-18d1-457a-9486-4e2a7169b12d" class="ctpl-c-faq_accordion-header">
                                        <div class="ctpl-c-faq_accordion-header-content">
                                            What happens to the funds contributed by individual employees who never utilize the CT Paid Leave program? Does the money follow the employee into retirement or another individualized benefit?
                                        </div>
                                        <div aria-hidden="true" class="ctpl-c-faq_accordion-header-button">
                                            <i></i>
                                        </div>
                                    </button>
                                        <div class="ctpl-c-faq_accordion-content" id="df76f8fc-18d1-457a-9486-4e2a7169b12d" role="region" aria-labelledby="accordion-id-df76f8fc-18d1-457a-9486-4e2a7169b12d" tabindex="0">
                                            <p>There is no reimbursement for employees close to retirement or for employees who never utilize the CT Paid Leave program.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Employees who are required to participate in the plan make contributions that are paid into a pool and become a permanent part of the Trust Fund. There are no individualized benefits under the plan.</p>
                                        </div>
